<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-11 01:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> dlnytfonsrh  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WESTPORT, Conn. (AP) -- America's domestic goddess says she's
moving from her country home.
</P>
<P>
   In a piece written for The New York Times Sunday magazine,
Martha Stewart said she's leaving this posh suburb of because she's
fed up with an ''unfriendly neighborhood atmosphere,'' a difficult
commute to New York City and the loss of the small-town feeling
Westport once had.
</P>
<P>
   Stewart said she is sad to think about leaving the town she has
lived in for the last 28 years.
</P>
<P>
   But Stewart, who has sometimes clashed with her neighbors over
filming her television show at her home, said Westport ''just
doesn't work'' for her any more.
</P>
<P>
   She laments the change from a small town where butchers knew
their customers' names to a place with a ''more elitist, and much
less charming, retail scheme.''
</P>
<P>
   Stewart says that although she used to be on personal terms with
her neighbors, today she knows very few of them. She talks of
offering fresh eggs or garden produce to newcomers, but being
rebuffed twice -- ''once with a slammed door!''
</P>
<P>
   ''As hard as it will be to leave my Westport home, I no longer
feel connected to the neighborhood, the neighbors or even the
town,'' Stewart wrote.
</P>
<P>
   Westport has been a celebrity enclave for years. Paul Newman and
Joanne Woodward live in town; so does singer Michael Bolton.
</P>
<P>
   Stewart says she will probably live in Manhattan full-time,
although she says she may end up moving to another town that is
closer to New York City.
</P>
<P>
   ''But wherever I end up, I'm sure that my current feelings of
frustration about Westport will eventually mellow to a fond liking.
After all, things change,'' she wrote.
</P>
<P>
   Stewart is chief executive officer of Martha Stewart Living
Omnimedia, a publisher of books and magazines, and producer of a
syndicated column and a TV program that gives homemaking and
entertaining tips.
</P>
<P>
   Susan Magrino, a spokeswoman for Stewart, said she will continue
to film her television show at her studio in Westport. Stewart
filmed the show at her home until 1998, when she opened a new
studio across town.
</P>
<P>
   Magrino also said Stewart has no immediate plans to sell her
house in Westport.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-04-11-00 0108 </TRAILER>
