<HEADLINE> Angels 6, Blue Jays 0  </HEADLINE>
By KEN PETERS, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Scott Schoeneweis, making his second
major league start, pitched a three-hitter and Troy Glaus hit a
three-homer to lead the Anaheim Angels over the Toronto Blue Jays
6-0 Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Garret Anderson hit a two-run double in the third inning and a
sacrifice fly in the seventh. Glaus' homer also came in the
seventh, against reliever Paul Quantrill.
</P>
<P>
   Schoeneweis (2-0), who pitched six innings to beat the New York
Yankees 12-6 last Wednesday, struck out four and walked four. He
allowed Marty Cordova's leadoff single in the fifth, Homer Bush's
two-out double in the sixth and Alex Gonzalez's leadoff single in
the eighth.
</P>
<P>
   A rookie reliever with Anaheim last year, Schoeneweis was 1-1
with a 5.49 ERA in 31 appearances spanning 39 1-3 innings.
</P>
<P>
   Chris Carpenter (0-2) gave up two runs and three hits in six
innings, but had trouble getting the ball over the plate and walked
eight. Of his 92 pitches, 47 were balls.
</P>
<P>
   The eight walks were one shy of the club record shared by five
pitchers. Carpenter was the last Blue Jays pitcher to walk nine --
last Aug. 16 in a 7-5 loss to Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   Mo Vaughn had a two-out single in the third, Tim Salmon walked
and Anderson doubled over the head of left fielder Shannon Stewart.
</P>
<P>
   Adam Kennedy's one-out single began a four-run seventh. Vaughn
doubled, Salmon was intentionally walked and Anderson's sacrifice
fly chased Pedro Borbon. Glaus drove Quantrill's first pitch over
the center-field fence.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Anaheim's Ramon Ortiz will make his first start of the
season despite having a slight tear of the labrum muscle in his
right (pitching) shoulder. Ortiz faces Toronto's Kelvim Escobar on
Tuesday night. ... The Blue Jays were 9-3 against the Angels last
season, going 6-0 at Toronto. ... Anaheim SS Gary DiSarcina, who
bruised his left thumb making a diving catch on Saturday, missed
his second straight game and is day to day.
</P>
