</P>
<P>
   New York's Larry Johnson was credited with a 3-pointer with 21.7
seconds left in the Knicks' 83-81 victory over Indiana on Monday
night. However, replays appeared to show Patrick Ewing getting a
hand on the ball and directing it into the basket as it was heading
for the rim. The Pacers argued frantically but to no avail.
SAME PRICE:
</P>
<P>
   Utah Jazz owner Larry H. Miller said Monday that ticket prices
won't increase for the 2000-01 regular season, the first time the
team hasn't raised prices since moving to the Delta Center in 1991.
