of the Timberwolves' 102-100 victory over Detroit on Monday night
for clashing with the officiating crew. Saunders was ejected after
he tossed his suit coat into the stands, ran onto the court and
went into a profanity-filled tirade.
SLUMPING:
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta lost its seventh in a row Monday night, 99-94 to Boston.
The Hawks haven't won on the road since Feb. 25 at Seattle, a
12-game drought.
SPEAKING:
</P>
<P>
