market, but we'll never get the benefit of the doubt like the
big-market teams like New York and Los Angeles. That's just the
league being the league. Enough is enough.'' -- Indiana's Reggie
Miller questioning the integrity of the league Monday night after
officials allowed a 3-pointer by New York's Larry Johnson with 21.7
seconds left, even though replays clearly showed Patrick Ewing
tipped it in. The Pacers ended up losing 83-81 to New York.
</P>
