<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nasdaq Drops 100 in Early Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Nasdaq Composite Index is off another 100
points in early trading today after losing more than 250 yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones industrial average is down 10. Gainers and losers
are evenly split on the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 Stock Index is down seven points.
</P>
<P>
   Concerns are being felt once again about earnings in the
high-tech sector.
</P>
<P>
   Those worries have led to a recent migration away from
technology shares and into more stable, lower-valued issues.
</P>
<P>
   Motorola shares will face some early selling pressure after the
company failed to top the so-called whisper estimates on Wall
Street.
</P>
<P>
   And earnings from the biotech firm Biogen fell short of
published estimates.
</P>
</TEXT>
