<HEADLINE> Delta To Start Santiago Flights  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA (AP) -- Delta Air Lines said Tuesday it will begin flying
to Santiago, Chile, on Nov. 1 as it continues to expand its Latin
American operations.
</P>
<P>
   The flights, on Boeing 767 jumbo jets, will be from Delta's main
hub in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Since 1997, Delta has increased its service to Central and South
America, offering 23 daily flights to 13 countries. The airline is
also seeking government permission to begin serving Bogota,
Colombia; Buenos Aires, Argentina; and Montevideo, Uruguay.
