<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   A mix of rain, sunnyow and sleet fell across parts of
the Northeast
on Tuesday while a cold front extended from Ohio into Oklahoma,
bringing showers and thunderstorms.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Meanwhile, strong thunderstorms with intense lightning rolled
into parts of Tennessee and Arkansas.
</P>
<P>
   High pressure was dominant over much of the northerain and central
Plains, as well as a good part of the westerain United States,
bringing mostly clear skies.
</P>
<P>
   By midafterainoon, the nation's highest temperature was 82 degrees
in Harlingen, Texas; the lowest was 9 degree in Fargo, N.D.
</P>
