<HEADLINE> Scripps' 1st Q Earnings Rise  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CINCINNATI (AP) -- The E.W. Scripps Co.'s first-quarter earnings
increased by 5 percent to $33.6 million, propelled by fast-growing
revenues at Home &AMP; Garden Television and the Food Network.
</P>
<P>
   The earnings were equivalent to 43 cents per share and included
expenses from the company's venture capital funds and gains from
sold-off operations. Without those one-time factors, earnings would
have been 45 cents a share.
</P>
<P>
   In the same quarter a year ago, Scripps earned $32 million, or
40 cents per share.
</P>
<P>
   Revenues increased 9 percent to $410.9 million from $376.3
million a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
   Television earnings were strong, led by a 54 percent growth in
revenues from Home &AMP; Garden Television to $51 million and 60
percent growth at Food Network to $22.2 million.
</P>
<P>
   Scripps increased Internet investments in its newspapers by
$800,000 from the first quarter of 1999. The 31 Scripps Internet
sites generated $4.9 million in revenue against costs of $8.1
million during the quarter.
</P>
<P>
   The Cincinnati-based company operates 20 daily newspapers, 10
broadcast television stations and the Home &AMP; Garden Television,
Food Network and Do It Yourself cable channels.
</P>
<P>
   Its operations also include Scripps Productions, a TV
programmer; United Media, which syndicates and licenses news
features and comics, and the Scripps Howard News Service.
</P>
<P>
   Scripps shares rose $1.06\ to $47.56\ in trading at 4 p.m. on
the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
</TEXT>
