<HEADLINE> Honda Lawnmowers Recalled  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- About 112,000 Honda lawnmowers were recalled
Tuesday because of the danger of fire from leaky fuel tanks, the
Consumer Product Safety Commission said.
</P>
<P>
   America Honda Motor Co. reported 25 cases of the tanks' seams
cracking or splitting, but no fires or injuries. The commission
said Honda voluntarily recalled the mowers.
</P>
<P>
   ''Harmony II'' and the model numbers HRT216, HRR216 or HRS216
are written on the front of the mowers. They are painted dark grey
with red fan covers.
</P>
<P>
   They were sold by Honda power equipment dealers and Home Depot
from May 1998 through January 2000.
</P>
<P>
   Honda power equipment dealers, who can be located by calling
1-800-426-7701, will make free inspections and repairs.
</P>
