<HEADLINE> ABC Pulls 'Wonderland' Off the Air  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- ABC has dropped its controversial drama
''Wonderland'' after just two airings.
</P>
<P>
   Leaving six episodes unaired, ''Wonderland'' will be off at
least through the May sweeps, according to ABC, with any future
after that undetermined.
</P>
<P>
   Set in the psychiatric ward of a fictional Manhattan hospital,
the gritty drama won almost universal critical praise, but,
scheduled against NBC's ''ER,'' it failed to win many viewers. Last
Thursday, its audience combined with that of CBS' faltering new
series ''Falcone'' added up to roughly half of the ''ER''
viewership in that time slot.
</P>
<P>
   Adding to its troubles, ''Wonderland'' drew criticism from
mental health professionals who said the series demonstrated
''reckless indifference'' to the mentally ill.
</P>
<P>
   Series creator Peter Berg responded that the show's purpose was
''to provide a catalyst for honest dialogue about the often
misunderstood and inaccurately represented world of the mentally
ill.''
</P>
<P>
   This Thursday, ABC will air a Peter Jennings-anchored news
special, ''Vanished,'' in the 10-to-11 p.m. EDT hour.
</P>
<P>
   Newsmagazine ''20/20 Downtown'' returns to that slot next week.
</P>
</TEXT>
