<HEADLINE> Eagles Re-sign Two Free Agents  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Linebacker James Darling and tight end
Luther Broughton signed one-year deals with the Philadelphia Eagles
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Darling, a second-round draft pick in 1997, started 10 games for
the Eagles at outside linebacker last season. He finished the year
with a career-high 98 tackles.
</P>
<P>
   Broughton had 26 receptions for 295 yards. He tied for the team
lead with four touchdown catches. Broughton, who was originally
drafted by the Eagles, returned to Philadelphia prior to last
season in a trade with Carolina.
</P>
<P>
   Quarterback Koy Detmer is the team's lone remaining restricted
free agent.
</P>
