<HEADLINE> Ripken Homers for Hit No. 2,995  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Baltimore's Cal Ripken homered in his
first at-bat Tuesday night, leaving him five shy of becoming the
24th player to reach 3,000 hits.
</P>
<P>
   Ripken, who began the season with 2,991 hits, hit his second
homer of the year on a 2-0 pitch in the second inning off Kansas
City's Chad Durbin. It was his 404th career homer.
</P>
