<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Replacement for Art Bell Found  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Popular overnight radio host Art Bell will be
replaced by Mike Siegel, a veteran talk radio broadcaster based in
Seattle, Premiere Radio Networks said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Bell, whose ''Coast to Coast AM with Art Bell'' attracts legions
of listeners with discussions of arcane mysteries and conspiracy
theories, said on March 31 that he was retiring from radio.
</P>
<P>
   Bell, 54, said he was leaving because of ongoing torment his
family has suffered since his son was kidnapped and raped in 1997
by a substitute teacher. He also said he was leaving because of
being falsely accused of being a child molester.
</P>
<P>
   ''Bell is looking forward to living an anonymous lifestyle as he
retires not only from radio broadcasting, but also all other forums
of media including book publishing, television, etc.,'' said a
statement from Premiere Radio Networks.
</P>
<P>
   Siegel, 55, will replace Bell on April 27. Siegel has been a
regular fill-in for radio hosts around the country. He is known as
an activist who advocated a consumer boycott of Exxon after the
1989 Valdez oil spill in Prince William Sound.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
