<HEADLINE> Iraqi-Syrian Pipeline Expansion  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAMASCUS, Syria (AP) -- French companies are working to expand an
oil pipeline between Kirkuk in northern Iraq and Syria's
Mediterranean port of Banias, France's visiting industry minister,
Christian Pierret, said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Pierret, who made the announcement during a joint news
conference with Syrian Oil Minister Mohammed Maher Jamal, gave no
details on the proposed expansion of the pipeline. Jamal refused to
answer a question on the project.
</P>
<P>
   The two men met earlier in the day to discuss technical
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
   France is involved in several major projects in Syria,
especially in oil, gas and phosphate sectors. France's Elf
Aquitaine is developing oil fields in northwestern Syria.
</P>
