<HEADLINE> Devil Rays' Vaughn Ejected  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Tampa Bay's Greg Vaughn was ejected
from Tuesday's night game against the Chicago White Sox for arguing
a called third strike.
</P>
<P>
   Vaughn argued the seventh-inning call by plate umpire Bill
Miller, then continued arguing after returning to the dugout.
</P>
<P>
   After his ejection, he ran back onto the field and made slight
contact with Miller before being sent to the clubhouse by Tampa Bay
manager Larry Rothschild.
</P>
<P>
   ''He did make contact with me ... it wasn't a lot,'' Miller
said. ''He just chested me. I'm going to write that when he came
out, he touched me. So we'll leave it at that. I'm sure they will
have a videotape of it.''
</P>
<P>
   Vaughn would not get into specifics of what was said between him
and Miller.
</P>
<P>
   ''You want respect, you give respect,'' Vaughn said. ''I'm a
grown man. You want respect, talk to me with respect. It's over
with. He thought they were good pitches, and I thought they were
bad pitches.''
</P>
</TEXT>
