<HEADLINE> ChiSox's Thomas Leaves Game  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Frank Thomas of the Chicago White
Sox might miss several starts after leaving Tuesday night's game
against the Tampa Bay Devil Rays in the sixth inning because of a
sore right foot.
</P>
<P>
   ''Obviously, the tendinitis is really flaring up,'' White Sox
manager Jerry Manuel said. ''We might not see him the rest of the
series. Maybe in a pinch-hitting role.''
</P>
<P>
   Thomas has been slowed by tendinitis on the inner heel of his
right foot and received a cortisone shot on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   ''I should notice a difference by the end of the week'' he said
before the game.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas had surgery on his right ankle last September. He was the
designated hitter Tuesday night and went 1-for-3 before Jeff Abbott
hit for him.
</P>
<P>
   White Sox third baseman Greg Norton left with a sore left
hamstring and could wind up on the disabled list, according to
Manuel.
</P>
</TEXT>
